     1	# Final Decision Memo - beyond-de-giorgi / run-008
     2	
     3	## Decision
     4	
     5	The winner is **Refined Chain 03 - Stochastic Transport Route With Early Mechanism And Coercivity Gate**.
     6	
     7	This is the best next chain to execute because it wins the two most important criteria simultaneously:
     8	
     9	- it has the highest presentable-result probability among the refined options;
    10	- it preserves the highest novelty ceiling while still having a sharp obstruction mode.
    11	
    12	Chain 01 remains the best floor-only screen, but its strongest likely output is mission infrastructure rather than the most distinctive next theorem-facing strike. Chain 02 remains valuable, but it is the most exposed to elegant repackaging and pressure/reconstruction collapse. The refined stochastic route is now disciplined enough that its downside is still useful, while its upside remains materially more original than the atlas route.
    13	
    14	## Why Chain 03 Wins
    15	
    16	### 1. Best balance of ceiling and floor
    17	
    18	The refined stochastic branch keeps a genuinely different structural reservoir: exact viscous-Lagrangian transport, circulation, backward-flow, and martingale observables. That is the highest novelty branch still on the board. At the same time, its refined version no longer mistakes exact representation for progress. It is now set up to fail usefully and early if the gain is only expectation-level, non-coercive, non-localizable, or solution-class fragile.
    19	
    20	### 2. Better execution fit than the original selector ranking suggested
    21	
    22	The selector was right that Chain 01 had the highest general floor, but the refined Chain 03 now has a tighter executable shape than before:
    23	
    24	- it starts from one named blowup mechanism rather than a menu;
    25	- it requires one observable to clear a coercivity or exclusion gate early;
    26	- it forces solution-class and localization viability before broad endpoint narration;
    27	- it demotes Tao-comparison to a secondary discriminator.
    28	
    29	That sequence is well matched to this system because it produces fast kill points and clear memo-grade outputs rather than inviting long descriptive drift.
    30	
    31	### 3. Failure is still highly reusable
    32	
    33	Even if the stochastic route fails, the likely failure modes are informative in a way that should guide later mission work:
    34	
    35	- expectation-only gain;
    36	- non-coercive martingale structure;
    37	- localization or stopping-time collapse;
    38	- solution-class mismatch near the singular regime;
    39	- prior-art redundancy;
