+# Exploration 001 Summary
+
+- Goal: freeze one honest mechanism-family-observable triple for the stochastic
+  branch, or say plainly that the record remains only a representation menu.
+- What I tried: read the Step 12 gate, the canonical chain, and the run-007 /
+  run-008 stochastic planning, selection, attack, judgment, and final-decision
+  files; extracted the sharpest supported burden, the best-supported family, and
+  the most concrete observable name on disk.
+- Outcome: inconclusive for a positive freeze; obstruction for Step-1 setup.
+- One key takeaway: the record narrows honestly toward
+  `local concentration of active scales` plus a `backward-flow / back-to-label`
+  family, but it never freezes a concrete observable beyond name-level planning.
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  - test whether a localized Constantin-Iyer / back-to-label identity can be
+    written in a solution class near the inherited weak-solution floor;
+  - ask whether that identity yields a pathwise or local concentration-exclusion
+    statement rather than only expectation bookkeeping;
+  - verify in the comparator memo whether the required gain really exceeds known
+    exact-but-nonclosing stochastic reformulation patterns.
+- Unexpected findings:
+  - `Constantin-Iyer` is the only explicitly named stochastic comparator
+    neighborhood I found in the local planning archive.
+  - The endpoint priority is more strongly frozen than the observable.
+- Computations worth doing later:
+  - derive the exact localized back-to-label / backward-flow identity under the
+    intended stopping and filtration setup;
+  - test whether any candidate term has one-sided or exclusionary content before
+    generic inequalities erase it.
